te last) won't try for (candidate last)'s budget goal," <i>the associated press</i>, 7/8/08) </p><p><b><u>just words #2: (candidate full) talks about leadership in the financial crisis but when the crisis first began, he refused to lead </u></b> </p><p><b>(candidate full): </b>"but then a little over a month ago, the bottom fell out. what happened in the financial markets was the final verdict on eight years of failed policies. and we're now going through the worst economic crisis since the great depression. a few weeks ago, we passed a financial rescue plan. it's a step in the right direction ... and as president, i'll ensure that you, the taxpayers, are paid back first. but we also need a rescue plan for the middle class ... starting with what we can do right now that will have an immediate effect." ((candidate last) for america, "american stories and american solutions" ad, 10/29/08) </p><p>• <b><i>the washington times</i>: "(candidate last) mum on market crisis." </b>"(PARTY NAME) presidential nominee sen. (candidate full) opted friday not to divulge details of his recovery plan for the financial crisis after a morning meeting with his top economic advisers -- fearing it would stir wall street jitters." (s.a. miller, "(candidate last) mum on market crisis," <i>the washington times</i>, 9/20/08) </p><p>• <b>(candidate full) did not make calls to round up votes for the economic recovery package. </b>abc's john berman: "the (candidate last) campaign has been hammering (candidate last) suggesting he did not take a leading role in the financial negotiations." sen. (candidate last): "at first, he didn't want to get involved. then, he was monitoring the situation." berman: "indeed, (candidate last) aides say he did not make any calls to help round up votes." (abc's "good morning america," 9/30/08) </p><p>• <b>(candidate full) "hinted that had he known earlier the deal was going down to defeat he would have worked the phones even harder." </b>"(candidate last) also hint